Request a free, no-obligation, <a href="/Ford-Edge-pricequotes.html">Ford Edge price quote</a> or choose any other model you&#8217;re interested in and receive the Buying Advice Team&#8217;s Insider Report for New Car Buyers.</div>




<p><strong>What is the Predicted Reliability:</strong></p>
<p>J.D. Power gives the Edge 3.5 stars for mechanical quality, and 4.5 stars for performance and design. Problems with the Edge include troublesome transmissions and brake drag. No recalls have been issued. Expect above average reliability.</p>

<p><br/><strong>Analysis Of Safety Ratings And Features:</strong></p>
<p>The Edge earned 4.5 stars in government frontal crash tests and 5 stars in side tests. It earned perfect IIHS tests and is one of their 2008 &#8220;Top Safety Picks.&#8221; Anti-lock brakes, full side airbags, and stability control come standard. Parking sensors are available on the SEL and Limited.</p>

<p><br/><strong>Pros and Cons:</strong></p>
<p>Pros<br/>
+ Bold styling<br/>
+ Powerful engine<br/>
+ Strong safety<br/>

<br/>
Cons<br/>
- Mediocre fuel economy<br/>
- Soft handling<br/>
- Some complex and cheaper interior features
</p>

<p><br/><strong>Head-To-Head Competition:</strong></p>
<p>The <a href="/Hyundai-Santa%20Fe-pricequotes.html">Hyundai Santa Fe</a> includes AWD and can carry more, but has 20 less hp. The <a href="/Saturn-VUE-pricequotes.html">Saturn VUE</a> includes AWD, but costs over a grand more. The <a href="/Toyota-RAV4-pricequotes.html">Toyota RAV4</a> Limited has a standard CD changer at the same price.</p>

<p><br/><strong>What Others Are Saying:</strong></p>

<p>&#8220;For the most part, I like the Ford Edge. I like the styling, I like the comfort, I like the features, and I like the value. I like the engine, though I&#8217;d be willing to trade horsepower for a little better fuel economy. I just don&#8217;t care for the isolated driving feel. The Edge may be the only radically styled SUV in Ford&#8217;s stable, but it&#8217;s not the only one on the market. Were the driving feel as radical as the rest of the car, I&#8217;m sure I&#8217;d like it a lot better.&#8221;<em> &#8211; <a href="http://suvs.about.com/od/for1/fr/07_Edgeag.htm" target="_blank">About.com</a></em></p>

<p>&#8220;This may be the hit Ford needs to get the turn-around plan moving.&#8221;<em> &#8211; <a href="http://www.theautochannel.com/news/2006/10/26/026660.html" target="_blank">The Auto Channel</a></em></p>

<p>&#8220;But do we like the Edge? Ford&#8217;s marketers mentioned a mythical man named &#8220;Phil&#8221; at whom the Edge is allegedly aimed. He&#8217;s 31, childless, active and on the go. In other words, he&#8217;s me. And I ain&#8217;t buying. If I wanted to sit in a highchair, I&#8217;d grab a CX-7. However, Element-owning Boomers who are tired of cruising PT just might snap-up the Edge up in droves. Ford&#8217;s sure hoping the roulette wheel comes up as red as their recent financial statements. Or Blazing Copper Metallic, to be more exact.&#8221;<em> &#8211; <a href="http://www.thetruthaboutcars.com/reviews/ford-edge" target="_blank">The Truth About Cars</a></em></p><br/>

<p>Read more about the 2008 Ford Edge at the <a href="http://www.fordvehicles.com/crossovers/edge/allnew" target="_blank">Ford</a> manufacturer web site.</p></div>

<br />

